description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting development opportunity has come up for a Band 5 Nurse, Social Worker or Occupational Therapist to join the Bradford and Airedale Early Intervention in Psychosis (EIP) service as a Care Coordinator with the Early Intervention Hub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This development post offers an opportunity to build experience and skills within a community EIP service through a period of preceptorship and a competency based CPD programme leading into a Band 6 position over a 12-month period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based within the Early Intervention hub, a dynamic service based at Culture Fusion in the centre of Bradford. The successful applicant will join an experienced, established and supportive specialist mental health team. Working closely within a Multi-Disciplinary-Team which includes staff with their own service user experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role focusses on specialist assessment for first episode psychosis, those at risk of developing psychosis (ARMS) and where indicated offering supportive interventions for up to 6 months. The service is committed to supporting staff with regular clinical and caseload management supervision and a culture of learning and ongoing progression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will take place 23rd November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have any questions regarding the post please contact Mick Mesa, Team Leader on 07525 873 699&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Mick Mesa&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Early Intervention Psychosis Team leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: mick.mesa@bdct.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07525 873 699&lt;/p&gt;
